genresAdvancedInfo.name: argentine jazz
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Argentine jazz is a vibrant and eclectic genre that draws inspiration from a variety of sources, including traditional Argentine folk music, tango, and American jazz. Musicians such as Diego Schissi and Juan Cruz de Urquiza are known for their innovative and improvisational approach to the genre, fusing together different styles and creating a truly unique sound.
